article.headline: Old Dominion 78, Towson 67
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Frank Hassell scored 15 points to lead Old Dominion to a 78-67 win over Towson on Tuesday night. Gerald Lee and Kent Bazemore each scored 14 points for the Monarchs (21-7, 13-3 Colonial Athletic Association). Keyon Carter finished with 13 points and a game-high seven rebounds. Old Dominion never trailed after the Tigers (7-19, 4-12) held a one-point lead with 15:58 left in the first half on layup by Josh Brown, who finished with 11 points. The Monarchs took their largest lead of the game at 63-46 on Lee's free throw with 8:49 to play. Towson would pull no closer than 11 points the rest of the way. Old Dominion shot 51.6 percent from the floor (33-for-64) compared to the Tigers, who shot 46 percent (23-for-50). The Monarchs also outrebounded Towson 39-28. RaShawn Polk led the Tigers with 16 points. Isaiah Philmore and Robert Nwankwo scored 11 points apiece.
